	     Harare - President Robert Mugabe must leave office on Sunday, the head of Zimbabwe's war veterans association said as pressure builds on the authoritarian leader to resign after a military takeover. "The army must finish with him today. He'd better give in to them now," Chris Mutsvangwa told reporters ahead of a crunch meeting between Mugabe and the generals who took control of the country. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  